{
  "stem": "13395.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And since my sister was not academically inclined, she tried first-- she wanted to work with flowers because of nature that we were introduced to.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But gardening was not flowers in-- in that town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was not for her.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So then she went for-- to learn hairdressing.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The family was in uproar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was not something that a nice Jewish girl would do.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my mother was determined that she should have a trade, that wherever we go, that she could work, find work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You mentioned that your mother came from quite a religious Jewish background.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "How would you define the religious atmosphere in your home?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well as I said, we observed all the holidays.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Friday night was Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Candles were lit.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was Shabbat dinner.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But living among non-Jews, the store was open on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You just did not close the store.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But at least Friday night was-- was kept.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I think that was typical of German Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Passover-- it was very difficult to get matzah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You had to go to another town and bring everything.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was no refrigeration.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So it-- it wasn't easy to get everything.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "However, the Seder, we used to have in our home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My grandmother wouldn't come because she didn't travel on Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she was too old to walk.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Hanukkah, I remember, was lighting the candles every night and then playing with the dreidel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the thing you could win would be a nut or a candy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There were no gifts every night like here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We played the dreidel, we got a nut.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the Purim, my mother would take us to Hindenburg or to the neighboring town, Chorzow, where there were more Jewish people, for Purim parties.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
